{"parentUuid":"e49ba03c-df03-4889-9448-15e9d9fb761c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"aa47f8eb58a90b448","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run the \"deep-research\" workflow.\n\nDeep research harness — fan-out web searches, fetch sources, adversarially verify claims, synthesize a cited report.\n\nWhen the user wants a deep, multi-source, fact-checked research report on any topic. BEFORE invoking, check if the question is specific enough to research directly — if underspecified (e.g., \"what car to buy\" without budget/use-case/region), ask 2-3 clarifying questions to narrow scope. Then pass the refined question as args, weaving the answers in.\n\nPhases:\n- Scope: Decompose question (from args) into 5 search angles\n- Search: 5 parallel WebSearch agents, one per angle\n- Fetch: URL-dedup, fetch top 15 sources, extract falsifiable claims\n- Verify: 3-vote adversarial verification per claim (need 2/3 refutes to kill)\n- Synthesize: Merge semantic dupes, rank by confidence, cite sources\n\nInvoke: Workflow({ name: \"deep-research\", args: \"Research AlphaEvolve from Google DeepMind (2025). Find primary sources: the DeepMind blog post, the white paper/PDF, and credible coverage. Need DETAILED, SPECIFIC, CITED facts about: (1) the architecture (evolutionary coding pipeline using an ensemble of Gemini LLMs Flash+Pro that mutate/edit code, combined with automated evaluators that score each candidate; how the evolutionary loop works — population, mutation via LLM diffs, selection by evaluator score); (2) the critical role of the verifier/evaluation function — AlphaEvolve only works on problems with a machine-gradable/automatically-verifiable objective function, why this is a fundamental constraint, what classes of problems it excludes; (3) concrete results — 4x4 complex matrix multiplication (48 vs 49 multiplications over Strassen), 0.7% recovery of Google datacenter compute (Borg), TPU circuit/arithmetic improvements, Gemini training kernel speedups, advances on ~50 open math problems, kissing number in 11 dimensions — with specific numbers and sources; (4) what AlphaEvolve CANNOT do — stated limits: does not improve its own LLMs/weights, requires a verifier, not applicable to problems lacking automated evaluation — quote DeepMind's own caveats. For each fact provide the exact source URL. Prefer deepmind.google, arxiv, the white paper. Return a structured list of falsifiable claims each with its URL.\" })"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"1c8255f0-0eb2-41ac-8282-ceb63f806893","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:16.135Z","sourceToolUseID":"toolu_01TqGByAXFrmfYCydp4CJ57h","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
