{"parentUuid":"8fa77b85-f8e5-4d2a-b71e-6eb58af612dc","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa47f8eb58a90b448","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01SrVkBLXvpsa1dVrbn7fVtF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FMg3mfjJ9bVH7CjeGhq6UD","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Search AlphaEvolve verifier role","prompt":"Use WebSearch and WebFetch to research the ROLE OF THE VERIFIER / EVALUATION FUNCTION in Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve (2025). I need specific, cited facts with exact source URLs.\n\nFocus on:\n- AlphaEvolve only works on problems with a machine-gradable / automatically-verifiable objective function (an automated evaluator that returns a score)\n- Why this is a fundamental constraint of the system\n- What classes of problems this EXCLUDES (problems that cannot be automatically evaluated, e.g. subjective/qualitative outputs, problems requiring manual experimentation or wet-lab work, anything without a programmatic scoring metric)\n- The exact phrasing DeepMind uses about \"automated evaluation metrics\", \"machine-gradable\", \"verifier\", \"evaluation function\"\n\nPrefer primary sources: deepmind.google blog post (\"AlphaEvolve a Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms\"), the arxiv white paper / DeepMind white paper PDF. Also credible coverage (Ars Technica, MIT Tech Review, etc.) for the framing of the constraint.\n\nReturn a list of falsifiable, specific claims. Each claim MUST have its exact source URL. Quote DeepMind's own caveats verbatim where possible. Do not write files — return findings as your final text message.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9436,"cache_read_input_tokens":5811,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9436,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":12318}}},"requestId":"req_011CcG22BJ37tz9rnNVRZGKY","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"87376167-e5da-4438-a204-cfac602dcb41","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:33.959Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"87376167-e5da-4438-a204-cfac602dcb41","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa47f8eb58a90b448","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01SrVkBLXvpsa1dVrbn7fVtF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YTm6utPXCPE3dMesXMgBvG","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Search AlphaEvolve results matrix math","prompt":"Use WebSearch and WebFetch to research the CONCRETE RESULTS on ALGORITHMS AND MATHEMATICS achieved by Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve (2025). I need specific numbers with exact source URLs.\n\nFocus on these specific claims and verify exact figures:\n- 4x4 complex-valued matrix multiplication using 48 scalar multiplications (vs Strassen's 49), the first improvement in 56 years over Strassen's 1969 algorithm\n- Advances on open math problems: applied to ~50 open problems in mathematics/analysis/geometry/combinatorics; rediscovered state-of-the-art in ~75% and improved on ~20%\n- The kissing number problem in 11 dimensions (new lower bound — find the exact number, e.g. 593)\n- Any other math results (e.g. Erdos minimum overlap, uncertainty principles, sum-difference sets)\n\nPrefer primary sources: deepmind.google blog post (\"AlphaEvolve a Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms\"), the arxiv white paper PDF (arxiv 2506.13131 or the DeepMind white paper). Cross-check numbers across sources.\n\nReturn a list of falsifiable, specific claims with exact numbers. Each claim MUST have its exact source URL. Do not write files — return findings as your final text message.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9436,"cache_read_input_tokens":5811,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9436,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_chan