{"parentUuid":"a6196bc9-15e3-4277-ad2a-78f316685889","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa47f8eb58a90b448","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01SrVkBLXvpsa1dVrbn7fVtF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01AVQZqnCfzKZvFRNdGX38Q5","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Search AlphaEvolve infra results","prompt":"Use WebSearch and WebFetch to research the CONCRETE RESULTS on GOOGLE INFRASTRUCTURE / HARDWARE achieved by Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve (2025). I need specific numbers with exact source URLs.\n\nFocus on these specific claims and verify exact figures:\n- Recovering 0.7% of Google's worldwide datacenter compute resources via a scheduling heuristic for Borg (Google's cluster management system), and that it has been in production for over a year\n- TPU circuit / arithmetic design improvements (e.g. removing/simplifying unnecessary bits in a Verilog/RTL arithmetic circuit, proposed for an upcoming TPU)\n- Gemini training kernel speedups (e.g. optimizing matrix multiplication / tiling heuristics in Pallas kernels, ~23% kernel speedup leading to ~1% reduction in Gemini's overall training time)\n- FlashAttention kernel optimization in the compiler (e.g. up to 32% speedup of the FlashAttention kernel implementation)\n\nPrefer primary sources: deepmind.google blog post (\"AlphaEvolve a Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms\"), the arxiv/DeepMind white paper PDF. Cross-check numbers.\n\nReturn a list of falsifiable, specific claims with exact numbers. Each claim MUST have its exact source URL. Quote DeepMind's wording where possible. Do not write files — return findings as your final text message.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9436,"cache_read_input_tokens":5811,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9436,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"out